I immediately sent an email to Millie's Cookies on the evening of the 13th, yet no one got back to me so I am forwarding you my original complaint:

This evening I have tried to purchase a Millie's Cookie giant cookie at three of your shops/stalls within The Trafford Centre. I travelled 35 miles specifically to buy one as I leave work this week and wanted to thank my staff. Due to work commitments The Trafford Centre is ideal due to its late opening times of 10pm. 

At approximately 7:50 I went to the Millie's stall that was advertising how the cookies are "made in 40 minutes", when asked if I could order one he said I was best going to the shop closer to John Lewis and ordering there as that's where they are made. At about 8:05 I got to the shop and was told that they had "run out" but the shop near the food hall should have some left so I should go there. As this was in the complete other direction the stall had sent me, I was quite irritated, but had no other option. At about 8:15 I got to the food court Millie's, to be told they "stopped serving at 8" for the giant cookies - something the shop upstairs didn't oblige to, something they didn't warn me of and something that was not advertised anywhere. And again, the cookies were being displayed in the window as an item that could be purchased. The staff were in no way helpful and told me if I were to order now they would have to cook it fresh - this problem baffled me with an hour and 45mins until closing. 

I feel extremely let down by all three stores and the customer service. I went out of my way to purchase one of your products as I think so highly of them and was left more than disappointed. As someone who has worked in retail myself, I can appreciate how important customer service is and I don't feel any of your members of staff or services were at their best.

Your menu on the one or twomeat is confusing and misleading. On the menu it says one/two meat or seafood + 2 veggies. And $2 charge if you add prawn. Literally, I only had one meat-which was beef. And prawn is not a meat. It is a seafood. Please have your menu straightened out and have an informative lady at the counter not just assuming that every customer knows your menu. 

Thank you.

I wanted to write to complain about the appalling service I received today at the cabin at bristol airport.  I arrived at approximately 1.00 pm and ordered a Caesar salad with bacon and a Chenin blanc.  I was told at 1 15 there wAs no lettuce so I would have to change my order.  I decided to leave.  As I reached the counter I noticed a box of lettuce and was told it had just arrived.  I decided to stay.  At approx 1 35 my wine arrived.  By now the restaurant was busy.  People arriving later than me had their food orders delivered.  I asked a waitress where my order was.  She claimed she plated it at around 1 15 and would check.   Within 10 mins a salad arrived (no bacon) I sent it back!  5 mins later it arrived and I have to say was perfectly acceptable.  By now more staff had arrived.  

When I arrived at the restaurant there were around 12 people, it later filled and most were served their food before me.  When I left we were down to about 12 again.  

I am really sorry that the service in this restaurant has led me to complain as I was pleased to find a quiet restaurant with a good menu.  I probably won t return and I guess it's back to Dexters from now on.

Yours sincerely

Jill Aburrow

My girlfriend ordered our food while I was at another store.  She did not know the currency conversion, so she did not realize she was ordering a club sandwich that costs $27 USD.  If she had known the true cost, she definitely would not have ordered the sandwich, as $27 is well overpriced. We decided not to complain or take it back, especially since we would not have time to have the re-order something different.  We figured it must be a great sandwich, and probably large.  To our surprise, the sandwich was not anything very special, and it was not even a full size sandwich; it was only slightly larger than a half size sandwich.  In the end, we felt we were not given nearly the full value for what we paid for, and we are discouraged from eating at O'Leary's again, out of principle.

I work at the airport and I know decent food takes time. Northpoint averages about an 8 min wait, its worth the wait. On my last visit, my order number was 13, I leaned against the post and waited patiently for my number to be called. I hear them call for order 12, time passes and I hear order 16.  Gee maybe I've gone deaf and missed my number. WRONG. I approach the pick up counter to see if my order is ready and see the cook grab a burger and put it on the grill, the cashier scurry around to the kitchen area reach into the freezer, grab onion rings and put them in the fryer, and all these things look like the order I placed 11 minutes ago.... Using my limited math skills, I figured 11+8(usual wait)+3(the time it took to walk)+5(find a seat and food cooling)=27 leaving me 3 minutes to actually eat the single burger and onion rings. I had to cancel my order or go hungry, which isn't an option when working with the public. I would have been better off not wasting my time and eating a bag of chips at least I would have had the time to finish them.

I reklamen var afbilledet en dip serveret i et mindre glas, hvilket jeg opfatter som væsentligt forskelligt fra den mayo dip af mrk. Heinz, jeg fik serveret i engangsplast-emballage. Jeg blev ikke af ekspedienten gjort bekendt med at mit valg af bolle eller dip betød en merpris. Altså burde jeg kun have betalt kr. 119,- for burger måltidet og ikke ekstra i alt kr. 11,- for dip og grovbolle. Min kæreste og jeg køre ofte i bil fra København til Nordjylland, og vi spiser fra tid til anden på Monarch. Det skal derfor ikke forstås negativt, når jeg skriver, at jeg ikke forventer "restaurations"-måltider på Monarch. Jeg synes imidlertid ikke, at omhandlende måltid var, hvad jeg burde kunne forvente. Jeg fandt anledning til at tage fotos af burgeren, og jeg har efterfølgende taget et foto af reklamen for samme burger. For mig er der stor forskel på, hvad jeg forventer og det jeg rent faktisk får.

This is a followup. I've already spoken to Amit Beri who is the Terminal Manager for Pearson Airport in Toronto. I gave him the specifics of the situation and he wanted to speak to me. I informed him that I was visiting my cousin for a couple days and my phone didn't have roaming so if it was okay with my cousin I could use his phone for this. I also showed all the online complaints about this place. Maybe that was enough but the place was still there when I left, nothing had seemed like it had changed and now that finally I'm back home I figured I'd send this off.

First off, you really don't make it easy to find you. I searched high and low on the internet to find this and it was only today when I sent a message to Amit did I bother looking up his email address which led me to foodtravelexperts.com and finally to here. If I were the suspicious type, which I am, I'd almost think that this was designed to prevent people from finding the parent company and allowing them to complain. But for the sake of being forthright, I'll let you know of my experience here. It's literally been almost three months and I'm still pissed about it.

 If there was a way to give zero stars I would. Back a couple months ago we were passing through Pearson and I was hungry so looking at the other options, which strangely were the same from restaurant to restaurant, we chose "True Burger Co." because the lineup was long and that usually indicates it's popular.

After spending ten minutes in line and it hardly moved we went and sat at the bar. A woman rudely asked if we were drinking anything because that was the only way we could sit there. I said sure, we ordered a couple of drinks, two cheeseburgers and an order of fries.

The food took some time and it looked like they were having trouble with their ordering system. More than once as we sat there waiting for our food somebody would come back saying they had forgotten something or didn't give them what they had ordered. A couple people just asked for their money back which was grudgingly given. This should have been our second clue that we shouldn't eat here but we had ordered and were drinking our overpriced airport beers so why change now?

The food arrives and it's just wrong. The burger looked okay. It had everything that we ordered on it but one bite and it all fell apart. The bun was cold and felt strange like it was made with something extra in it to make it fluffy. The meat was overly processed to the point of having no discernable texture. It was just soft and your teeth sank through it. It was also salty as hell. It literally tasted like it had been stored in a salt bath before throwing it in the microwave to heat up a bit. Yes, there was a lack of grilling on it. Or maybe it had kissed the flattop just enough to give it a slight browning before being nuked to hell.

The fries however were decent but it's really hard to mess up fries.

I couldn't finish and neither could my girlfriend. It was absolutely disgusting and the worst part was the price. For the privilege of eating a nuked cheeseburger, decent fries and expensive bottle of beer it cost us almost $50.00. There was no tip because honestly the server didn't deserve one.

I've worked service. I know about service and I get that sometimes you're busy but this woman wasn't. She spent most of her time standing around, getting snippy with the customers and not once did she ask us how the burger was. When it came time to pay she was busy talking with what I assumed was a friend as they were sitting at the bar with no drink or anything in front of them. So make of that what you will. It took her five minutes to realize we were waiting and then just gave us the bill without asking if we wanted anything else. My guess is she's been this way since the start and knows that once people taste the food, they don't want anything else.

And the absolute worst part about this is I tried to find the company online. They have no online presence. I mean none other than through the airport which leads me to believe it's not a chain so much as it's something Pearson has developed in house. I contacted Pearson directly because I needed to complain and got the attention of the Terminal manager Amit Beri. His e-mail is Amit.Beri@foodtravelexperts.com. This is the only contact I've had. He contacted me once concerning this asking to speak with me, but since I'm not from Toronto and was travelling it was difficult to do. I showed him the online reviews of the place and said if my cousin whom I was staying with was willing to share his phone so we could talk I'd be willing to do that.

He never contacted me again. That was a little more than three weeks ago. I'm back home now and I'm pissed. Nobody should be able to get away with this kind of service in today's world. It's unacceptable and the fact that this person couldn't take the time to actually contact us for more information and to see what he could do to make things right is even worse. I didn't want a free meal because that would involve eating there again. I didn't want an apology. What I wanted was a guarantee that they would look into this and take matters in hand. So far, nothing.

So as a warning, avoid True Burger Co in Pearson airport Intl terminal. You'll thank me later.
